            <title>[JOHNZON-322] johnzon-jsonschema: BaseNumberValidation cannot support negative numbers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JOHNZON-322</link>
                <project id="12315523" key="JOHNZON">Johnzon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;BaseNumberValidation&lt;/tt&gt; is the parent class of all number validations and such validations need to support negative numbers.&lt;br/&gt;
 For instance, trying to validate with a -1 &lt;tt&gt;MinimumValidation&lt;/tt&gt; will fail when val is &lt;tt&gt;-1&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;0&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Related code:&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/johnzon/blob/master/johnzon-jsonschema/src/main/java/org/apache/johnzon/jsonschema/spi/builtin/BaseNumberValidation.java#L40-L42&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/johnzon/blob/master/johnzon-jsonschema/src/main/java/org/apache/johnzon/jsonschema/spi/builtin/BaseNumberValidation.java#L40-L42&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
